cs.DC, cs.CR, cs.DS, cs.DB, cs.CE 

The paper discusses the computational challenges of analyzing large amounts of genomic data generated by high throughput sequencing platforms. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also discusses privacy concerns related to genomic data, which suggests a possible fit with cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The use of blockchain technology and cryptocurrency also suggests a possible fit with cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.DB (Databases). Finally, the use of volunteer grid computing suggests a possible fit with cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science).
